Pretty much every expert in the field says the project is a sure thing.
The biggest obstacle to the world’s fusion-energy future is funding, Sauthoff says.
ITER isn’t the world’s only nuclear fusion project.
“ITER will deliver,” says Juergen Rapp, a plasma physicist who works at Oak Ridge but isn’t involved in the ITER project.
“If you’re underfunded, you also waste money,” he says.
